data.description: Discover a hidden gem in the vibrant and eclectic neighborhood of Atwater Village, where the past seamlessly blends with the present. This incredible triplex offers a one-of-a-kind investment opportunity or a charming oasis for owner-occupied buyers seeking a taste of authentic Los Angeles living. Front unit 1,1 middle unit 2,1 and rear unit 2,1 total 1,540 SF with a lot size of 5,398 and ZONED for RD3. Two of the units can possibly be delivered vacant, negotiable. Located in OPPORTUNITY ZONE great potential tax benefits for investors / developers with lots of upside potential. (2 units will be delivered vacant.) call agent for details. (Current first loan is at 3.75 % FHA. It can possibly be assumed or offer este buy down for loan. Check with your lender.)    This property boasts three distinct units, each offering a unique blend of modern amenities and vintage charm. Whether you're an investor looking for a steady rental income stream or an owner-occupier wanting to live in one unit while renting the others, this triplex provides endless potential. Features include: 1 car attached garage for one unit, washer dryer hook ups, long driveway for parking, back yard perfect for entertaining or small gatherings, plenty of windows that emit lots of natural light, middle unit has been remodeled, newer roof, new electrical panel and plumbing. Move in ready.     Nestled in the heart of Atwater Village, this triplex is the epitome of location, location, location. Enjoy easy access to trendy cafes, boutiques, art galleries, Whole Foods, Americana, Momeed, Berg Acting Studio and parks - all within walking distance. Plus, you're just minutes away from Griffith Park and the LA River, providing endless outdoor recreation options. Proximity to the 5 and 2 freeways, as well as  transportation options, makes commuting a breeze and allows residents to easily explore the greater Los Angeles area.
